---
# ============================================================
# Baseline NetworkPolicies
# ============================================================
# K3s enforces NetworkPolicy out of the box via its embedded kube-router
# network-policy controller (active by default alongside the Flannel CNI).
# No policies are shipped by default, so the pod network is otherwise flat:
# every pod can reach every pod, across all namespaces.
#
# This manifest installs a conservative starter baseline: deny ALL ingress
# in three namespaces, while leaving egress open — so DNS resolution and
# normal outbound traffic keep working, but unsolicited inbound to these
# workloads is blocked (limits lateral movement / direct pod access).
#
# What is NOT affected:
#   - DNS:        pods still egress to kube-dns in kube-system (no deny there).
#   - Probes:     kubelet liveness/readiness probes (node-to-pod) are exempt.
#   - Egress:     all pods can still initiate outbound connections.
#
# Caveat: once you install an ingress controller (in its own namespace), it
# will be blocked from reaching services in `default`. Add an ingress-allow
# policy at that point (see the ansible-k3s README for an example).
# ============================================================

# 1. default namespace — isolate workloads deployed here by default.
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-ingress
  namespace: default
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
    - Ingress
---
# 2. ceph-csi-operator-system — the CSI driver exposes no network endpoints
#    to other pods; deny inbound as defense-in-depth. This namespace holds
#    the Ceph credentials Secret (csi-rbd-secret / csi-cephfs-secret).
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-ingress
  namespace: ceph-csi-operator-system
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
    - Ingress
---
# 3. metallb-system — speakers announce via ARP/L2 and do not need inbound
#    from workloads.
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-ingress
  namespace: metallb-system
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
    - Ingress